column2: A library optimized for concise and principled data graphics and layouts.

column5:
brush: fix d3 event typenames for HTMLDocument target (#920)

When instantiating multiple charts with targets of type HTMLDocument instead of id ('#viz'),
brush mousedown and mouseup events were registered with the same typename: `mousedown.[object HTMLDivElement]`
breaking the brushing feature.

Using the unique chart uid from the 'data-mg-uid' attribute to name to global event listeners fixes this while also working for normal id targets.
Avoid collapsing when selecting a too small range (#905)
Make list of options accepted by metricsgraphics machine-readable (#893)
judge decimals is set or not by isNumeric (fixes #794) (#901)

Make it harder to pass in data to metricsgraphics line charts that gets clobbered (fixes #896)

We set index and line_id properties on the data passed in so we can do some
lookups on these objects later. This isn't optimal, but is hard to fix
properly given the current state of the code. Workaround this by wrapping
the properties with `__`, making it less likely they'll get clobbered.
Simplify code to set a line id / index property on each datum in the series
Add highlighting option for point charts (#853)
Add an example of using popper.js to show a tooltip (#894)
Fix some minor jshint linter errors
Remove existing line if data is empty (fixes #890) (#891)
Support click callbacks for point charts (#889)
Remove gulp-util dependency and upgrade jshint (#888)
Make click to zoom out behaviour optional (#887)
Don't let rollover and markers overlap (fixes #839) (#876)
Only publish files in dist/ to npm
Add a version script to package.json
Allow releasing to npm by creating a tag (#869)
Fix source files missing from gulp build file
change to use 2 equals to check an attr is null or undefined (#868)
add an optional callback for brushing (fixes #866) (#867)
Persist selection in overview plot when zooming (fixes: #855) (#857)
Fix example rendering on front page

More changes to improve x axis time formatting (#863)

In some cases we would still be using hours when we should be using
days to label the x axis tickets in a time series (e.g. for a 7
or 14 day interval).
Serve website from root of gh-pages branch
use travis ci to auto deploy the examples page to gh pages (#862)
set user-select: none on SVG elements (fixes #852) (#856)
Add time range example of a "few years"

Handle years-long time differences better when drawing x axis (fixes #848)

Increase the threshold at which we display the x axis in terms of years
(for ranges of around 2 years, this could mean that we display the same
year multiple times on the x axis, due to the way d3 decides on the
number of ticks).

This required some follow-on changes to the way we decide to add a
secondary year marker to the x axis.
Remove unused variable from mg_add_x_axis_rim function
Process xax format at beginning instead of multiple times when rendering ticks
basic brushing and zooming feature for line and point charts (#851)

Don't overwrite user-specified decimals parameter when formatting y axis (fixes #844) (#847)

The decimals specification is supposed to be used for the rollover, it makes
sense to use it as a default value when formatting an axis, but only as input.

* Add IDE section with intellij files to .gitignore
Add an option to select lines with areas of a multi-line chart (#830)

Handle case where min_x is specified as 0 (fixes #729) (#840)

We were treating this case the same as if min_x was specified as `null` (the default) which is not correct.

fixes #597. args.min_y_from_data presented a number of implementation problems. The main issue was that the plot bounds were not contingent on the range between the max and min y, so the inflation of the max and min for the purposes of plot bounds were contingent on the magnitude of the data. Large refactoring of how line rollovers function under the hood. Primarily about moving away from using mg-line1-color as a selector. getting rid of the -color part of the class means that the selectors for rollovers are purely about selection, not color. This allows us to do things like color lines using a new argument: colors, which takes an array, and colors the lines as they are ordered by accessor or by placement in the data argument. This is primarily targeted toward #503, but required this refactoring and reworking so that nothing else breaks.
